name: Bryant Park fire
summary: Multiple fires have plagued holiday markets in New York City, including two at Bryant Park Winter Village within two weeks. A recent fire at the market started in a kiosk's cooking oil, destroying three stalls and damaging others. Fortunately, no one was injured, and investigators have ruled the fire accidental. Despite this, the string of fires has raised concerns about safety and fire prevention measures at these popular holiday attractions.

name: Norwegian Cruise ship man overboard
summary: A male passenger has gone overboard from a Norwegian Cruise Line ship bound for the Bahamas. The search for the 51-year-old man has been called off after proving unsuccessful. The ship, which departed from Florida, had been on a Caribbean cruise when the incident occurred. The man was on vacation with his family at the time of his disappearance, prompting concern and an immediate search operation. Despite efforts, the man could not be located, and the search has been officially discontinued.

name: Gleyber Torres
summary: The Detroit Tigers have acquired infielder Gleyber Torres from the New York Yankees on a one-year, $15 million contract. Gleyber Torres, a former All-Star with the Yankees, had previously declined a contract offer from the Washington Nationals in part due to a potential position change. Torres' move to the Tigers marks his departure from the Yankees organization, where he played as a second baseman. Industry insiders had previously indicated that a return to the Bronx was unlikely for Torres.
